Hence we should have expected dissimulatorem rather than simulatorem. But it is clear that every act ol dissimulatio involves a corresponding simulatio. Thus Socrates, to use the words oi Cicero Brut. 5 292, omnium se rerum inscium fingebat et rudem,· and therefore was a simulator properly so called.
